Package: scEasyPip
Title: Automated Seurat Pipeline for scRNA-seq analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Theo",
                  family = "Botella",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "tb2928@cumc.columbia.edu",
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0331-2491"))
Description: Automated scRNA-seq analysis using 10x output and the Seurat package. Perform Quality Control, Normalization, Dimensionality Reduction, Visualization, Clustering and DGE using Seurat. Assign cell-types to cluster based on your own markers. Merge or integrated Seurat objects. Cluster cells using Transcription Factors activity with Viper and Dorothea packages.
Depends:
  R (>= 4.1),
  Seurat (>= 4.0.0),
  clustree (>= 0.4.3)
Imports:
  SeuratObject,
  patchwork,
  MAST,
  ggplot2 (>= 3.3.0),
  sctransform (>= 0.3.2),
  umap,
  stringr,
  ggraph,
  dorothea,
  dplyr,
  viper,
  grDevices,
  stats,
  utils 
